<br>
Another point, some of the spells or abilities discussed around here should be deity specific, for example, Nife followers should have special healings / undead curses, Brell followers should get nice stackable defensive / utility buffs, Prexus followers better group healings, Quellious receive some kind of long duration stuns, stackable group regens for tunare's knights, area stuns for Karana's palies, and Marr followers get attack (Mithraniel) or defense (Erollisi) buffs... All those buffs wouldn't stack between them, for example brell's rock skin wouldn't stack with Tunare's blessing... That would be so EXTREMELY cool... but Verant should keep an eye on balancing out, we don't want people to just shout for &quot;group looking for warrior, innoruk SK or Prexus worshiping paladins PST) we're talking about a pair or three deity specific spells / abilities, not a full new line per deity or leaving great spells like instrument of nife only to nife worshiping pals (destroying the rest's chance to solo)... This could apply too to clerics, sks, rangers, necros, druids, shammies, bsts and other deity dependant classes (dunno if I left any out, I'm talking about non-agnostic classes like warriors or thieves). <br>
<br>
Even multi-god spells would be nice, for example, Rodcet nife and the Marrs specially hate undeads, so they could get some special questable anti-undead spell that both could use ( the reweard for a special triggered crusade on the plane of disease, for example), Prexus and Brell are both elemental gods, so they could get an special interplanar quest spell (Shield of elements, or mudveil, or something like that), or a pair of spells that DID stack, and that would be a nice combined effect (mudveil and waterward, could be a self only DS and small selfheal everytime the paly was hit, by themselves they're not much, but combined they'd be terribly efficient).. Karana and Quellious could get something too (Tranquility and storms... hehe I'll leave it to your imagination, but sounds like some terrible area stuns or even mezzes heh).<br>
<br>
Of course we'd be talking about epic level quests for those spells. Also, if these lines where implemented, it would be nice that verant did a pair of small changes to EQ's game system: letting more spells stacking on a player, and giving players a pair more of spell slots (no more &quot;the spell won't stack!&quot; messages due to having buffed up too much the player, please!!).<br>
<br>
